    <item>
      <title>Rsync including hidden files</title>
      <link>https://www.it-quicktasks.com/rsync-including-hidden/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 06 Jun 2020 09:21:14 +0800</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://www.it-quicktasks.com/rsync-including-hidden/</guid>
      <description>If you need to rsync those hidden directories or files starting with dot, do it something like below (not the trailing /)
rsync -avz -e ssh --progress user@source-server:/somedirA/ somedirB/  See https://stackoverflow.com/questions/9046749/rsync-not-synchronizing-htaccess-file</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Rsync Excluding Inner Folders</title>
      <link>https://www.it-quicktasks.com/rsync-excluding-inner-folders/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 25 Oct 2018 09:24:00 +0800</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://www.it-quicktasks.com/rsync-excluding-inner-folders/</guid>
      <description>In this example, we want to sync example.com except &amp;lsquo;example.com/temp_uploads&amp;rsquo;
rsync -avz --exclude &#39;example.com/temp_uploads&#39; example.com /var/www_backups  NOTE: exclude files are always relative.
details in https://www.thegeekstuff.com/2011/01/rsync-exclude-files-and-folders</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Rsync via Ssh</title>
      <link>https://www.it-quicktasks.com/rsync-via-ssh/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 25 Oct 2018 09:21:14 +0800</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://www.it-quicktasks.com/rsync-via-ssh/</guid>
      <description>rsync -avz -e &amp;quot;ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -o UserKnownHostsFile=/dev/null&amp;quot; \ --progress /var/www/html/example.com/docroot me@example.org:/var/www/html/example.org/  </description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Rsync With Specific Key</title>
      <link>https://www.it-quicktasks.com/rsync-with-specific-key/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 25 Oct 2018 09:20:07 +0800</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://www.it-quicktasks.com/rsync-with-specific-key/</guid>
      <description>rsync -Pav -e &amp;quot;ssh -i $HOME/.ssh/somekey&amp;quot; username@hostname:/from/dir/ /to/dir/  </description>
